<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INSTRUMENTS - 1000 SERIES Starting 02/08/2004 - CLUSTER FAILURE DIAGNOSTICS - FUEL LEVEL SENSOR/GAUGE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="0">
        <title>FUEL LEVEL SENSOR/GAUGE</title>
        <para>If the electric fuel gauge shows a reading which is suspected of being incorrect, insure all electrical
            connections are clean, tight, unbroken and are not shorted. If this fails to remedy the problem, the fuel
            level sensor must be checked. The fuel level sensor is a float/resistive potentiometer type with the
            following output characteristics at different fuel levels.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>Before checking the fuel gauge, be sure the vehicle has been parked on a level surface long enough
                    for the fuel level to stabilize. In cold weather insure the vehicle interior is warmed up.
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
